首次亲眼看到 青蛙的神秘死亡
Was one of the first to witness a mysterious die-off of frogs.

151
00:11:38,064 --> 00:11:41,700
有一天 我走过小溪 发现一只死蛙
Lips: one day I was walking down the stream, and I found a dead frog,

152
00:11:41,768 --> 00:11:43,902
我有点担心
And, you know, I was a little concerned,

153
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:46,372
但是在接下来几个星期 我又发现了几只死蛙
But...over the next couple of weeks I found a couple more.

154
00:11:46,439 --> 00:11:49,141
我下一年回来时 青蛙都不见了
I went back the next year, and they were gone.

155
00:11:49,209 --> 00:11:51,510
青蛙不见了
The frogs had disappeared.

156
00:11:51,578 --> 00:11:53,345
其实 同样的事情
Essentially the same story played out

157
00:11:53,413 --> 00:11:55,814
也发生在几年后的巴拿马边境
A couple of years later across the border in panama.

158
00:11:59,085 --> 00:12:02,755
Lips博士在中美洲看到死蛙的时候
Argo: while Lips was witnessing die-offs in central america,

159
00:12:02,822 --> 00:12:05,424
同样的一幕也在澳大利亚上演
A similar story played out in australia.

160
00:12:05,492 --> 00:12:08,193
直到确认了壶菌病
By the time chytrid was identified,

161
00:12:08,261 --> 00:12:12,965
全世界的两栖动物已经崩溃了
Amphibian populations had already crashed throughout the world.

162
00:12:15,502 --> 00:12:17,536
壶菌已经偷偷地进入
The fungus has been stealthy,

163
00:12:17,604 --> 00:12:22,908
那些没开发 但又拥有地球上最珍稀物种的区域
Reaching into untouched areas that hold some of earth's greatest treasures.

164
00:12:25,712 --> 00:12:27,946
青蛙可能是渺小的
Frogs might be diminutive,

165
00:12:28,014 --> 00:12:31,684
后果却是严重的
But the stakes are enormous.

166
00:12:31,751 --> 00:12:38,090
医学已经证实 青蛙是小金矿
Medical science has begun to realize that frogs are little gold mines.

167
00:12:38,158 --> 00:12:44,063
为了应对感染 很多青蛙的皮肤能够分泌化学物
To ward off infection, most frogs secrete chemicals from their skin.

168
00:12:44,130 --> 00:12:45,931
有时青蛙甚至是有毒的
They can actually be poisonous.

169
00:12:45,999 --> 00:12:49,001
这些明亮的颜色警告掠食者
These bright colors are a frog's warning to predators

170
00:12:49,069 --> 00:12:51,203
青蛙是危险的食物
That they could be a dangerous meal.

171
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:57,176
青蛙皮肤上的化合物 已经使医学重现生机
The compounds on frog skin have turned medical science around.

172
00:12:57,243 --> 00:13:00,412
从小青蛙皮肤提取的化合物
An extract from the skin of this little frog blocks pain

173
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:06,618
止痛的效果比吗啡好 而且不会令人上瘾
More effectively than morphine -- and it's not addictive.

174
00:13:06,686 --> 00:13:10,389
青蛙皮肤的性质 可应用到各个领域
The properties of frog skin are being explored for everything

175
00:13:10,457 --> 00:13:13,392
例如治疗感染和防止艾滋病
From treating infections to preventing HIV.

176
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:17,930
我们才刚开始挖掘这个小宝藏
We've just begun to mine these little treasures,

177
00:13:17,997 --> 00:13:21,834
现在青蛙却衰减了 速度比我们的研究速度快得多
And now they're slipping away faster than we can study them.

178
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:29,908
但是这对全球生态系统的影响更大
But the impact on earth's ecosystems is even more troubling.

179
00:13:29,976 --> 00:13:33,212
Karen Lips博士回到位于巴拿马中部的 前研究基地
Karen Lips has returned to her former study site

180
00:13:33,279 --> 00:13:36,081
她要测量这些地区的变化
In central panama to measure the changes.

181
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:40,586
没有青蛙 这里静得可怕
Without the frogs, there's an eerie silence.

182
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:43,255
在El Cope保护区
In El Cope reserve,

183
00:13:43,323 --> 00:13:47,159
只剩下一座水泥青蛙雕塑
A concrete statue may be all that remains

184
00:13:47,227 --> 00:13:50,662
记录了巴拿马引人入胜的金蛙
Of panama's spectacular golden frog.

185
00:13:50,730 --> 00:13:53,799
青蛙大灭绝之前 这里是个好地方
Lips: before the big crash, this was a great place.

186
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:58,404
我估计这里大概有 64种两栖动物
I think our total list here was something like 64 species of amphibians.

187
00:13:58,471 --> 00:14:00,806
无论你走到森林的哪个地方
It didn't matter really where you went in the forest,

188
00:14:00,874 --> 00:14:03,075
你都能找到青蛙 地面上、叶子上
You would find them on the ground, on the leaves,

189
00:14:03,143 --> 00:14:04,710
你能听见青蛙在树冠上
You'd hear them up in the canopy.

190
00:14:04,778 --> 00:14:08,213
无论你走过哪条小径和溪流
You could walk any trail, any stream,

191
00:14:08,281 --> 00:14:10,382
你都能听到青蛙日夜叫个不停
And you would hear frogs calling day and night.

192
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:16,422
现在 这里一个青蛙也没有了
And now, you know, there's just nothing here anymore.

193
00:14:16,489 --> 00:14:18,657
壶菌病具有多米诺效应
Argo: chytrid is having a domino effect.

194
00:14:18,725 --> 00:14:21,293
青蛙位于食物链的中部
Frogs sit right in the middle of the food chain.

195
00:14:21,361 --> 00:14:26,832
没有青蛙 其它物种也会灭绝
Without them, other creatures are disappearing, too.

196
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:31,070
我们才刚开始了解 没有青蛙
Lips: we're just beginning to understand what a forest is like

197
00:14:31,137 --> 00:14:33,706
森林会如何运作、变成啥样
And how it functions without frogs.

198
00:14:33,773 --> 00:14:36,241
现在所有的蝌蚪都死掉了
Ever since all the tadpoles disappeared,

199
00:14:36,309 --> 00:14:38,777
这些小溪真的很滑
These streams have been really slippery.

200
00:14:38,845 --> 00:14:42,081
地面长满了绿藻
There's green algae growing all over the place.

201
00:14:42,148 --> 00:14:44,883
这是青蛙和蝌蚪灭绝后
It's just another example of the big changes that we see

202
00:14:44,951 --> 00:14:47,152
发生的巨大变化的一个例子
After all the frogs and tadpoles disappear.

203
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:50,556
蝌蚪不仅吃绿藻
The tadpoles not only eat the algae,

204
00:14:50,623 --> 00:14:52,624
蝌蚪还会扰动沙泥
But they also disturb all the sand and the mud,

205
00:14:52,692 --> 00:14:54,860
因此沙泥附着物被水流带走
And so all that gets flushed out with the current --

206
00:14:54,928 --> 00:14:56,829
现在这里没有蝌蚪了
And now there's no tadpoles,

207
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:59,398
我们看到昆虫也有变化
We see changes in some of the insects, as well.

208
00:14:59,466 --> 00:15:02,201
这里的生态系统变化很大
We're seeing lots of big changes in these ecosystems.

209
00:15:02,268 --> 00:15:08,474
青蛙灭绝影响到鱼类、水质 蛇类、鸟类........ 你来想吧
It's affecting fish, and water quality, snakes, birds -- you name it.

210
00:15:08,541 --> 00:15:12,211
基本上 我们观测到的一切都改变了
Basically everything we've measured has changed.

211
00:15:14,948 --> 00:15:17,049
壶菌病正在蔓延
Argo: chytrid is on the move.

212
00:15:17,117 --> 00:15:20,319
壶菌病从中美洲向北蔓延
While it's sweeping down through central america,

213
00:15:20,387 --> 00:15:23,389
壶菌病也从南美洲向北蔓延
It's also traveling north from south america.

214
00:15:23,456 --> 00:15:26,225
只有巴拿马的一个小地方
There's only a small area left in panama

215
00:15:26,292 --> 00:15:28,827
至今没有受到壶菌感染
That still seems to be chytrid-free.

216
00:15:31,998 --> 00:15:34,767
巴拿马运河以北 两小时的路程
Two hours south of the panama canal,

217
00:15:34,834 --> 00:15:38,337
有一叫做Burbayar的小森林
There's a small patch of forest called Burbayar.

218
00:15:38,405 --> 00:15:46,278
这里的青蛙 依然按照几百万年以来 形成的方式生活
For the frogs here, life plays out as it has for millions of years.

219
00:15:46,346 --> 00:15:51,583
壶菌逐渐逼近 奇迹有待出现
While chytrid draws closer, miracles are still unfolding.

220
00:15:51,651 --> 00:15:58,824
老爸已经守卫孩子两个多星期了
This father has been guarding his young for two weeks now.

221
00:15:58,892 --> 00:16:03,796
附近叶子上的蝌蚪却没有护卫
The tadpoles on a nearby leaf don't have a guardian.

222
00:16:03,863 --> 00:16:08,534
这些蝌蚪较成熟 但仍然需要几天时间才能孵化
They're more mature, but still days from hatching.

223
00:16:10,136 --> 00:16:14,340
健康的栖息地 有许多掠食者和食物
A healthy habitat is full of predators -- and prey.

224
00:16:14,407 --> 00:16:20,112
无论大小 每种生物都扮演着自己的角色
No matter how big or small, every creature plays a role.

225
00:16:26,319 --> 00:16:28,821
森林拥有数以千计的昆虫种类
The forest holds thousands of insect species.

226
00:16:28,888 --> 00:16:32,291
有些昆虫几个小时就毁掉一窝蛙卵
Some can destroy an egg clutch in a matter of hours...

227
00:16:43,036 --> 00:16:46,305
即使入侵者还没触及卵窝
Even if an intruder doesn't have a taste for eggs,

228
00:16:46,373 --> 00:16:48,874
这个老爸依然奋勇保护
This father is fiercely protective.

229
00:16:58,618 --> 00:17:00,686
虽然有些物种不保护孩子
Though the other species doesn't guard its young,

230
00:17:00,754 --> 00:17:02,788
孩子已经具备另一种防卫术
It's developed another defense --

231
00:17:02,856 --> 00:17:05,791
面对攻击 蝌蚪会努力挣扎开来
When attacked, the tadpoles will break free,

232
00:17:05,859 --> 00:17:09,895
使蝌蚪至少有斗争的机会
Giving them at least a fighting chance.

233
00:17:25,879 --> 00:17:27,079
在这里的溪流
Here in the stream,

234
00:17:27,147 --> 00:17:32,618
蝌蚪花很多时间 吃绿藻和小植物
The tadpoles will spend most of their time feeding on algae and small plants.

235
00:17:35,288 --> 00:17:40,359
一系列迷人的生存技能 使青蛙勇敢生存了几百万年
A fantastic array of survival tactics has allowed frogs to brave the millennia.

236
00:17:40,427 --> 00:17:43,862
但是 壶菌与其它任何掠食者都不同
But chytrid is a predator like none other --

237
00:17:43,930 --> 00:17:46,799
壶菌蔓延很快
And it's moving in fast.

238
00:17:46,866 --> 00:17:48,467
时间紧迫
Lips: the clock is ticking --

239
00:17:48,535 --> 00:17:51,637
自从92年这里第一只青蛙死掉后
And that's really what it's felt like more than anything

240
00:17:51,705 --> 00:17:54,206
我们真正需要的是速度
Since that first frog in '92, is the rush --

241
00:17:54,274 --> 00:17:59,712
在壶菌感染之前 尽快地救出尽可能多的青蛙
The rush to get out, to do as much as you can before another site goes.

242
00:17:59,779 --> 00:18:01,680
Lips和她的学生们
Argo: Lips and her students

243
00:18:01,748 --> 00:18:03,782
在Burbayar森林建立了 一个新的研究基地
Have established a new study site here at Burbayar.

244
00:18:03,850 --> 00:18:10,456
他们希望 壶菌病还没有蔓延到这里
They're hoping that chytrid, and the BD that causes it, haven't arrived yet.

245
00:18:10,523 --> 00:18:12,858
我们在这里试图获取更多的数据
Lips: we're here to try and get more data to figure out

246
00:18:12,926 --> 00:18:15,160
以确认发生了什么事 壶菌病是怎样来到的?
What is happening -- how does this thing get around?

247
00:18:15,228 --> 00:18:18,931
我们可以阻止壶菌病吗?
Can we stop it?

248
00:18:18,998 --> 00:18:27,339
森林里有青蛙、昆虫和蛇 看上去很健康
Argo: the forest appears to be healthy, with frogs, and insects, and snakes...

249
00:18:27,407 --> 00:18:30,943
但这种情形还能维持多久呢?
But for how much longer will it remain intact?

250
00:18:32,846 --> 00:18:36,648
使青蛙健康生活的栖息地 远远不够了
Lips: we're running out of places where frogs are healthy.

251
00:18:36,716 --> 00:18:39,685
我们估计 十年后巴拿马所有的青蛙都会灭绝
We estimate, within ten years all of panama will be gone.

252
00:18:39,753 --> 00:18:42,354
我指的是高海拔地区
We're talking upland areas,

253
00:18:42,422 --> 00:18:46,392
但是就算你走得快 壶菌病也持续蔓延
But as fast as you move, it's continuing its passage.

254
00:18:46,459 --> 00:18:48,060
我抓到一个青蛙
Woman: I got a frog.

255
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:54,500
一旦我们抓到青蛙 我们就测量青蛙的体温
As soon as we catch a frog, we take its body temperature,

256
00:18:54,567 --> 00:18:58,904
因为在气候变化及其对青蛙的影响方面 存在争议
Because there's a debate about climate change and how it's affecting frogs.

257
00:18:58,972 --> 00:19:01,040
33.5℃.
33.5度

258
00:19:01,107 --> 00:19:03,442
接着我们用棉签檫拭青蛙
Next we're going to swab it,

259
00:19:03,510 --> 00:19:05,744
并把棉签样品送回实验室 检测可以告诉我们
And we'll send this sample off to a lab, and they'll tell us

260
00:19:05,812 --> 00:19:08,247
这个青蛙是否感染了壶菌
Whether or not this frog is infected with BD.

261
00:19:08,314 --> 00:19:10,916
好的 现在我们抓住小腿
All right, so we're just going to take this little q-tip

262
00:19:10,984 --> 00:19:12,317
檫拭青蛙皮肤
And swab the frog.

263
00:19:12,385 --> 00:19:16,221
我们檫拭青蛙的腹部和腿
We do his belly, we do his feet.

264
00:19:16,289 --> 00:19:20,125
如果上面有壶菌 棉签会沾上它 我们带回实验室
If there's any BD, it'll pick it up, and we send this off to the lab,

265
00:19:20,193 --> 00:19:23,829
检测结果会表明 这是青蛙是否感染了壶菌
And the lab will tell us if BD is on this frog.

266
00:19:23,897 --> 00:19:25,497
好的 你走吧 伙计
All right, i'm gonna let you go, buddy.

267
00:19:25,565 --> 00:19:29,702
我们认为这个地方还算健康
Lips: we think this site is still clean.

268
00:19:29,769 --> 00:19:31,103
快看
Look at that --

269
00:19:31,171 --> 00:19:33,539
这是Rhinobothryum Bovallii蛇
That's Rhinobothryum Bovallii.

270
00:19:33,606 --> 00:19:35,274
非常罕见
They're really rare.

271
00:19:35,342 --> 00:19:36,475
这条好大
That's a big one.

272
00:19:36,543 --> 00:19:38,077
它以青蛙为食
They're a frog-eater.

273
00:19:38,144 --> 00:19:39,945
它正出来找吃的 你看它舌头轻吐
He's out foraging, you can see him tongue-flicking.

274
00:19:40,013 --> 00:19:48,354
一旦壶菌驾到 此蛇也可能和青蛙一样灭绝
Argo: once chytrid arrives, this snake may well disappear along with the frogs.

275
00:19:48,421 --> 00:19:53,692
基于Lips博士的研究结果 他们要采取紧急措施
Based on what Lips finds here, they might take emergency measures.

276
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:56,662
如果有必要 我们会把青蛙放到
Lips: if we have to, we will put some frogs

277
00:19:56,730 --> 00:20:00,466
囚禁地加以保护 以应对壶菌的最终到来
Into captivity as a safeguard against the eventual arrival of the fungus.

278
00:20:00,533 --> 00:20:07,272
三年前 生物学家在中美洲就是这样做的
Argo: this is exactly what took place in central panama, three years ago.

279
00:20:07,340 --> 00:20:10,743
壶菌病逐渐逼近
With chytrid fast approaching,

280
00:20:10,810 --> 00:20:14,146
生物学家从周围的森林中收集青蛙
Biologists evacuated frogs from the surrounding forest.

281
00:20:14,214 --> 00:20:16,949
这些“难民"离雾林是如此的近
These refugees are so close...

282
00:20:17,017 --> 00:20:20,786
却又是如此的远
And yet so far from their cloud forest.

283
00:20:20,854 --> 00:20:26,825
山脚有一栋简陋的建筑 作为庇护所
At the foot of the mountains sits a humble building that's serving as an ark.

284
00:20:26,893 --> 00:20:30,095
El Valle两栖动物保护中心（EVACC）
The El Valle amphibian conservation center

285
00:20:30,163 --> 00:20:34,299
是休斯顿动物园发起的国际计划
Is an international project launched by the houston zoo.

286
00:20:34,367 --> 00:20:37,436
EVACC保护了58种青蛙
"EVACC" shelters 58 species of frogs --

287
00:20:37,504 --> 00:20:40,706
有些是地球上的稀有种类
Some of the rarest on earth.

288
00:20:40,774 --> 00:20:44,276
这个美丽的金蛙是 巴拿马的独有品种
This beautiful golden frog is unique to panama.

289
00:20:44,344 --> 00:20:48,013
金蛙没有耳膜 通过摆臂交流
It lacks eardrums, and communicates by waving its arms.

290
00:20:48,081 --> 00:20:52,284
巴拿马人认为金蛙是好运
They're considered good luck by panamanians,

291
00:20:52,352 --> 00:20:58,957
但是 金蛙可能会因为壶菌而灭绝
But because of chytrid, they may be gone from the wild.

292
00:20:58,992 --> 00:21:05,364
Edgardo Griffith和他的妻子Heidi Rs共同管理这个中心
Edgardo Griffith runs the center with his wife, Heidi Rs.

293
00:21:05,432 --> 00:21:08,600
他们要模拟雾林
They have to try to replicate the cloud forest --

294
00:21:08,668 --> 00:21:12,237
光线、温度、湿度 所有条件都有适当
Light, temperature, humidity -- everything has to be right.

295
00:21:12,305 --> 00:21:16,942
要喂食很多个月 这是没完没了的挑战
And feeding so many mouths is a never-ending challenge.

296
00:21:25,218 --> 00:21:29,621
我刚刚漂洗了蚯蚓 因为它们身上可能有壶菌
We just rinse them off, just because the worms might have chytrid on them.

297
00:21:29,689 --> 00:21:34,660
不经过消毒 我们不会把任何东西 如灰尘
We try not to put anything, like dirt, without disinfecting it

298
00:21:34,728 --> 00:21:37,696
放进这间屋子
Before putting it inside the building.

299
