These are the guys who are applying it, they're out there picking it.

457
00:31:24,150 --> 00:31:25,984
溴化甲烷是一种薰剂
Methyl bromide is a fumigant,

458
00:31:26,052 --> 00:31:28,454
人们把薰剂泵入土壤
Something they pump into the soil.

459
00:31:28,521 --> 00:31:30,456
伙计 这个大家伙是什么?
What are some of the other big ones, you guys?

460
00:31:30,523 --> 00:31:32,624
二嗪农 还有阿特拉津（除草剂）
Diazinol... Some atrazine...

461
00:31:32,692 --> 00:31:37,763
所有这些化合物都会流进河里 就像这条河
This will all end up in the river that we're working in here.

462
00:31:44,170 --> 00:31:47,272
就像我们来到某处灌木
It might look like we're out in the bush somewhere,

463
00:31:47,340 --> 00:31:50,275
但是两边15尺开外就是农田
But 15 feet on either side, we're surrounded by agriculture,

464
00:31:50,343 --> 00:31:53,579
废物都跑进河里了
And the runoff ends up in this river.

465
00:31:53,646 --> 00:31:56,015
藻类就是养分充沛的结果
All the algae is the result of all the nutrients,

466
00:31:56,082 --> 00:31:58,317
因为农田需要很多肥料
Because a lot of fertilizers are used in agriculture,

467
00:31:58,385 --> 00:32:03,022
一旦肥料进入水里面 藻类就繁荣生长了
And once those fertilizers get into the water, you get these blooms of algae.

468
00:32:03,089 --> 00:32:05,190
我认为 藻类不是河水清洁的证明
I wouldn't say it's the sign of a healthy river.

469
00:32:05,258 --> 00:32:08,894
这种地方 我们通常能找到有害的免疫系统
This is a site where we typically find compromised immune systems --

470
00:32:08,962 --> 00:32:11,463
蝌蚪无法应对疾病
Tadpoles that aren't able to fight off disease.

471
00:32:13,967 --> 00:32:16,623
我们的研究表明
Our data so far suggests that

472
00:32:16,624 --> 00:32:21,340
杀虫剂导致压力荷尔蒙的增加
The mixture of pesticides causes an increase in stress hormones,

473
00:32:21,408 --> 00:32:23,742
这些压力荷尔蒙引起抑制免疫反应
And those stress hormones cause immunosuppression,

474
00:32:23,810 --> 00:32:27,146
最终导致生物无法应对任何一种的病原体
Which leads to the inability to respond to any kind of disease pathogen.

475
00:32:28,581 --> 00:32:34,586
在研究化学废水的同时 Hayes也盯上了另外一个元凶
Argo: while investigating chemical runoff, Hayes stumbled on another culprit.

476
00:32:34,654 --> 00:32:37,356
我们来到萨利纳斯河
Hayes: we started going to the salinas river

477
00:32:37,424 --> 00:32:39,458
寻找红腿的本地蛙
Looking for the native red-legged frog,

478
00:32:39,526 --> 00:32:43,929
我们发现红腿蛙完全被牛蛙取代
And it turns out that it has been completely replaced on the river by bullfrogs.

479
00:32:43,997 --> 00:32:46,465
这种具有侵略性的牛蛙
This invasive bullfrog itself

480
00:32:46,533 --> 00:32:49,168
其数量也在减少 当地人是其中一个原因
Is one of the causes for decline in man of these areas.

481
00:32:49,235 --> 00:32:50,436
所以我们研究牛蛙
And so we're studying them

482
00:32:50,503 --> 00:32:52,571
牛蛙在这里过得并不好
In areas where they're not doing well

483
00:32:52,639 --> 00:32:56,608
我们试图了解 造成本地红腿蛙灭绝的原因
To try to understand what may be driving some of the native species to extinction.

484
00:32:56,676 --> 00:33:02,114
企业家从东海岸把牛蛙运来这里
Argo: entrepreneurs transported bullfrogs from the east coast,

485
00:33:02,182 --> 00:33:05,317
希望养殖牛蛙 作为人类的食物
Hoping to farm them for food.

486
00:33:05,385 --> 00:33:07,986
然而 企业家却放出了这种肉食动物
Instead, they unleashed a carnivore

487
00:33:08,054 --> 00:33:11,290
牛蛙已经毁掉了加利福尼亚的本地蛙
That has decimated california's native frogs.

488
00:33:11,358 --> 00:33:18,764
即使强壮的牛蛙 也不能适应河水里的毒物
It seems that even the tough bullfrog isn't doing so well with the toxins in this water.

489
00:33:18,832 --> 00:33:23,602
回到实验室 Hayes研究另外一种非本地蛙
Back at berkeley, Hayes is studying another non-native.

490
00:33:23,670 --> 00:33:27,940
非洲爪蛙一度用于人类的妊娠试验
African clawed frogs were once used in human pregnancy tests.

491
00:33:28,008 --> 00:33:31,510
当瓜蛙变得无用时 就被抛弃了
But when they became obsolete, many were discarded.

492
00:33:31,578 --> 00:33:35,147
这些瓜蛙来自加利福尼亚附近的水流
These were collected from streams around california.

493
00:33:35,215 --> 00:33:36,615
我们切开一只瓜蛙
Hayes: we're removing an invasive frog,

494
00:33:36,683 --> 00:33:40,352
通过研究瓜蛙 来了解两栖动物数量下降的原因
And we're studying them to try to understand declining amphibians.

495
00:33:40,420 --> 00:33:43,155
Hayes研究化学品的影响
Hayes is testing the effects of chemicals

496
00:33:43,223 --> 00:33:45,891
阿特拉津 一种普通的除草剂
Like atrazine, a common herbicide.

497
00:33:45,959 --> 00:33:50,829
这些动物 我们都切除了雌性染色体
Hayes: we have a whole family of animals where we've eliminated the female chromosome.

498
00:33:50,897 --> 00:33:52,498
01号标本
Woman: specimen zero-one.

499
00:33:52,565 --> 00:33:55,334
这些在基因上 都是雄性动物
Hayes: these animals that we know are genetic males

500
00:33:55,402 --> 00:33:58,237
我们把这些动物 一直和阿特拉津接触
Have been exposed to atrazine for their entire life,

501
00:33:58,304 --> 00:34:00,205
很多这些基因上的雄性动物
And many of these genetic males

502
00:34:00,273 --> 00:34:02,341
现在都变成雌性动物了
Now are turning into females.

503
00:34:02,409 --> 00:34:03,742
你可以看到 他会产卵
You can see he's got eggs

504
00:34:03,810 --> 00:34:05,644
看上去好像是液囊
That kind of look like they're in a sac.

505
00:34:05,712 --> 00:34:08,347
其实是黄色的卵 而且快要产下来了
These are actually yolked eggs, ready to be laid.

506
00:34:08,415 --> 00:34:11,183
我们可以改变性别比例
What's happening is you're skewing sex ratios,

507
00:34:11,251 --> 00:34:13,452
你可以打破基因瓶颈
You can get genetic bottlenecking,

508
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:16,121
这会造成毁坏 坦白说
Which can cause crashes, and quite frankly,

509
00:34:16,189 --> 00:34:17,456
如果你在基因上是男的
If you're a genetic male,

510
00:34:17,524 --> 00:34:20,125
长大后变成男人 这非常好
It would be nice if you developed as a genetic male,

511
00:34:20,193 --> 00:34:22,995
现在我们有一种存在环境中的 很普通的化学品
And now we have a chemical very common in the environment,

512
00:34:23,063 --> 00:34:25,064
可以有效地改变动物的性别
That's effectively sex-reversing animals.

513
00:34:25,131 --> 00:34:27,066
我要向你展示 令人惊奇的情景
I'm going to show you something pretty amazing,

514
00:34:27,133 --> 00:34:29,468
科学而言
Scientifically speaking.

515
00:34:34,974 --> 00:34:38,510
值得注意的是这一对
The one that's sort of remarkable is this pair.

516
00:34:38,578 --> 00:34:40,846
它们都是雄性动物
These are both males.

517
00:34:40,914 --> 00:34:43,449
底部的那个变成雌性动物
The one on the bottom acting as the female

518
00:34:43,516 --> 00:34:45,951
我们动情地叫它"Darnell."
We affectionately refer to as "Darnell."

519
00:34:46,019 --> 00:34:49,788
他的基因是雄性的 却不仅在行动上像雌性
He's a genetic male that not only acts like a female,

520
00:34:49,856 --> 00:34:52,091
他还会像雌性那样产卵
He lays eggs like a female.

521
00:34:52,158 --> 00:34:57,229
他/她一生都暴露于阿特拉津杀虫剂
He/she has been exposed to atrazine all of her -- his/her life --

522
00:34:57,297 --> 00:34:58,931
我不知道怎样称呼它
I don't even really know how to reference it.

523
00:34:58,998 --> 00:35:01,000
这是“Darnell”第三次产卵
This is Darnell's third clutch.

524
00:35:01,067 --> 00:35:04,303
所以Darnell有男女后代 我们已经把这些后代养大
So Darnell has sons and daughters that we've grown up.

525
00:35:04,371 --> 00:35:06,271
你可以看看底部的卵
You can see eggs in the bottom.

526
00:35:06,339 --> 00:35:08,607
其实这是他今天的第二次卵了
This is actually her second clutch for today.

527
00:35:08,675 --> 00:35:13,779
他/她交配已经超过24小时
He/she has been copulating for getting close to 24 hours now.

528
00:35:13,847 --> 00:35:17,516
这可能是我研究中 看到的最引入注目的事情
This is probably one of the most remarkable things i've seen in my work,

529
00:35:17,584 --> 00:35:19,418
但我的心情很复杂
But I personally have mixed emotions.

530
00:35:19,486 --> 00:35:21,434
我对科学着迷
I'm very excited about the science

531
00:35:21,435 --> 00:35:25,024
我试图了解变性机理 但另一方面
And trying to understand the mechanism, but on the other hand,

532
00:35:25,091 --> 00:35:27,626
我又非常担心 这种污染物非常普遍
I am worried -- this is the most common contaminant

533
00:35:27,694 --> 00:35:29,228
地下水、地面水和饮用水中都有
In ground and surface water, and drinking water,

534
00:35:29,295 --> 00:35:33,932
使动物变性的阿特拉津的 浓度水平
And the level of atrazine that it took to make this male turn into a female

535
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:37,236
只有我们饮用水的 规定值的三分之一
Is three times less than what's allowed in our drinking water.

536
00:35:37,303 --> 00:35:40,539
我认为全球两栖动物数量下降
I really think that the global amphibian decline

537
00:35:40,607 --> 00:35:43,575
正在暗示人类的健康问题
Is telling us something about human health.

538
00:35:43,643 --> 00:35:47,713
人类用水中的毒物水平远远高于青蛙
Argo: the toxins in our waters are reaching well beyond frogs.

539
00:35:47,781 --> 00:35:51,950
畸形繁殖的报道常常见于
Reproductive abnormalities have been reported in everything from

540
00:35:52,018 --> 00:35:55,621
鳄鱼、北极熊 以及人类
Alligators to polar bears... To humans.

541
00:35:55,689 --> 00:35:57,122
这并不只是青蛙的事情
Hayes: it's not just a problem with frogs

542
00:35:57,190 --> 00:35:58,557
我们也应该关注
We should be concerned about.

543
00:35:58,625 --> 00:35:59,925
造成青蛙畸形的水
The water that's causing their problems

544
00:35:59,993 --> 00:36:01,226
人类也在饮用同样的水
Is the same water that we're drinking

545
00:36:01,294 --> 00:36:03,162
并用同样的水来灌溉农作物
And using to water our crops.

546
00:36:05,131 --> 00:36:07,333
无论是青蛙还是人类
Argo: frog or human,

547
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:11,236
我们都呼吸同样的空气 饮用同样的水
We all breathe the same air and drink the same water.

548
00:36:11,304 --> 00:36:14,673
为了青蛙和人类的利益 专家一致认为
For their sake and ours, experts agree --

549
00:36:14,741 --> 00:36:18,610
我们必须行动起来 没有时间了
We have to take action, and there's no time to lose.

